  "$comment_schema": "Cross-impl golden vectors for the Pages filter-primitive evaluation (#1908 slice 2, increment a). Shape: { rows[], scenarios[] }. Each row is a page; scenarios apply an AND-composed list of FilterPrimitive wire objects and assert the SET of matching page ids. Only the matching-id set is compared cross-impl (representation-stable). Asserted by BOTH src-tauri/.../pages_filter_primitive_conformance_tests.rs (real query path) and src/lib/tauri-mock/__tests__/filter-primitive-conformance.test.ts (mock metaRowMatchesFilter).",
  "$comment_scope": "Covers the PURE-over-row primitives evaluable without global mock state: Stub, HasNoInboundLinks, Priority, LastEdited(Range), plus AND-composition. LastEdited Rolling/OlderThan are intentionally excluded — they resolve against the wall clock ('now' / new Date()), so a golden fixture cannot pin them. Orphan (link seeding) and Tag/HasProperty (mock-state seeding) are separate #1908 increments.",
